shit: 2:8: warning: A test with -a or -o is obsolescent.
     2 |  [ -f a -a -f b ]
       |         ^~ here.
note: Join two tests with && or || instead.
shit: 3:3: warning: A negated -z is just -n.
     3 |  [ ! -z "$x" ]
       |    ^~ here.
note: Test with -n instead.
shit: 4:3: warning: A negated -n is just -z.
     4 |  [ ! -n "$y" ]
       |    ^~ here.
note: Test with -z instead.
